org.xbib.elasticsearch.index.analysis.combo

Class ReaderClonerDefaultImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.xbib.elasticsearch.index.analysis.combo.ReaderClonerDefaultImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ReaderCloneFactory.ReaderCloner<Reader>

    public class ReaderClonerDefaultImpl
extends Object
implements ReaderCloneFactory.ReaderCloner<Reader>
    Default, memory costly but generic implementation of a Reader duplicator.

    This implementation makes no assumption on the initial Reader. Therefore, only the read() functions are available to figure out what was the original content provided to the initial Reader.

    After having read and filled a buffer with the whole content, a String-based Reader implementation will be used and returned.

    This implementation is memory costly because the initial content is forcefully duplicated once. Moreover, buffer size growth may cost some more memory too.

    Author:
    ofavre

        Initialize or reinitialize the cloner with the given reader. The implementing class should have a default no arguments constructor.

        Remark: The given Reader is now controlled by this ReaderCloner, it may be closed during a call to this method, or it may be returned at first call to ReaderCloneFactory.ReaderCloner.giveAClone().
